0.body: Hey there! Welcome to the book for the space_shooter_rs game. It aims to serve as the primary source of documentation for those interested in contributing to a game using the Amethyst game engine . This book is being actively updated. So there may be sections that are still under construction.
0.title: Introduction

1.body: In space_shooter_rs, you play as a spaceship defending an objective. The goal of the game is to survive levels by destroying enemies, collecting consumables, buying items, and defeating the final boss. In this section you can find detailed information about the enemies, consumables, items, enemies, allies, and bosses in the game. gameplay of space_shooter_rs
1.title: Gameplay

13.body: In general, the process for contributing goes like this: Pick an issue to work on Setup your development environment Write the patch, create a PR, and request a review
13.title: Contributing code

14.body: Take a look at the issues list and choose an issue you'd like to work on. Issues labeled as good first issue are a great way to get started with the codebase. Make sure to claim the issue by commenting you'd like to work on it and mentioning either @cdsupina or @tigleym . Ask questions if something is unclear about the issue you are working on. Creating your own issue If the existing issues aren't what you're looking for then feel free to create a new issue! This can be fixing a bug, improving documentation, or a proposal to implement a new feature. Whatever the purpose is, please make sure to create an issue for it describing what you intend to do and why. If you need help identifying what the focus of your issue should be, feel free to mention either @cdsupina and @tigleym . We can help identify the sort of work that might be involved for your issue. This step is important because we want to make sure the work behind each pull request has context and intent.
14.breadcrumbs: Pick an issue to work on
14.title: Pick an issue to work on

15.body: This part of the process involves getting a local copy of the project and setting up your development machine to be able to build and run it. Since this is a game built with the Amethyst game engine, it's important that Rust is setup and have the proper dependencies installed on your dev machine. Fork the space_shooter_rs project. Create a local clone of the fork Run the game Once you're able to successfully build the game, you can start writing some code!
15.title: Setting up your dev environment

16.body:
Before writing your patch, branch off develop: git checkout -b <branch-name> develop When finished writing your patch, save and commit your work: git add
git commit -m "meaningful commit message" Make sure to run cargo fmt to ensure your work is formatted correctly and that no warnings are present when you run cargo build. The CI checks will fail if build warnings are present in your PR. Now that your patch is ready for review, you can push your changes: git push and create that PR for review! Please make sure to link the issue you selected earlier in the PR's description.

2.body: In space_shooter_rs you control a spaceship character. You can move around, shoot, use abilities, and buy items from the store. Key Action W w_key Accelerate up. S s_key Accelerate down. A a_key Accelerate left. D d_key Accelerate right. Space space_key Fire blast. Left left_key Barrel roll left. Right right_key Barrel roll right. 1 one_key Buy shop item 1. 2 two_key Buy shop item 2. 3 three_key Buy shop item 3. Escape esc_key Pause the game.
2.title: Controls

3.body: In the future, the player will be able to choose to play as one of many characters. Each character has a unique special ability. Name Image Special Ability Juggernaut juggernaut Barrel roll to the left or right.
3.title: Characters

4.body: Items can be purchased from the shop (bottom right). They grant the player permanent augmentations. Name Description Steel Barrel steel_barrel Gives player collision damage immunity while barrel rolling. Plasma Blasts plasma_blast Increases fire rate and damage. Hazardous Reactor hazardous_reactor Increases maximum speed. Warp Thruster warp_thruster Increases acceleration and deceleration. Quadrupedal Tentaclover quadrupedal_tentaclover Grants chance to critical hit. Defense Satellite defense_satellite Increases maximum defense. Double Barrel double_barrel Grants double blasts. Yithian Plague yithian_plague Grants chance to poison. Spice spice Decreases barrel roll cooldown time. Enhanced Plating enhanced_plating Increases maximum health by a factor. Structure Reinforcement structure_reinforcement Increases maximum health. Blast Size Enhancer blast_size_enhancer Increases size of shot blasts.
4.title: Items

5.body: Consumables have a chance to be dropped from enemies upon being destroyed. Name Image Description Health Wrench health_wrench Grants health to the player. Defense Wrench defense_wrench Grants defense. 1x Currency money_1_wrench Grants 1 currency. 5x Currency money_5_wrench Grants 5 currency.
5.title: Consumables

6.body: Enemies can damage the player and the defense. Upon being destroyed they have a chance to drop consumables. Name Image Description Drone drone_enemy Most basic enemy in the game. Moves towards the bottom of the arena and does defense damage on arrival. Pawn pawn_enemy Moves towards the bottom of the arena at a reduced speed and does defense damage on arrival. Periodically fires a blast. Strafer strafer_enemy Strafes left and right towards the bottom of the arena at a reduced speed and does defense damage on arrival. Periodically fires a blast.
6.title: Enemies

7.body: Allies provide a temporary objective. Make sure they survive and you will be rewarded. Name Image Description Hauler hauler_ally Moves towards the bottom of the arena at a very reduced speed and grants defense on arrival.
7.title: Allies

8.body: Bosses arrive at the end of a stage. Destory them to move on to the next stage. Name Image Description Repeater repeater_boss WIP.
8.title: Bosses
